Here's a minimal API endpoint handling multipart form uploads with multiple images and a description:

```csharp
// Program.cs

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size to 50 MB (default is ~30 MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Read the multipart form with a 50 MB limit
    var form = await request.ReadFormAsync(new FormOptions
    {
        MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 50 * 1024 * 1024
    });

    var description = form["description"].ToString();
    var files = form.Files.GetFiles("images");   // matches <input name="images" />

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No images uploaded.");

    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        // Validate content type
        if (!file.ContentType.StartsWith("image/"))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not an image.");

        var destPath = Path.Combine("uploads", $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{Path.GetExtension(file.FileName)}");
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(destPath);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);
        saved.Add(destPath);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, uploadedFiles = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery();          // required for minimal APIs accepting form data without a token

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **`ConfigureKestrel`** — raises the server-level body limit (Kestrel defaults to ~30 MB).
- **`FormOptions.MultipartBodyLengthLimit`** — controls the per-read multipart limit.
- **`form.Files.GetFiles("images")`** — grabs all files submitted under the `images` field name.
- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** — without this, .NET 8 minimal APIs reject form POSTs that lack an antiforgery token (fine for APIs; re-enable for browser forms with CSRF protection).

A matching `curl` test:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "description=Vacation photos" \
  -F "images=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "images=@photo2.png"
```
